The paper proposes a novel clustering concept based on jointly learned nonlinear transforms with priors on information loss and discrimination. This concept is applied to an image clustering task, indicating a likely fit with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of discriminative priors suggests a potential fit with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the use of numerical experiments suggests a potential fit with neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
